dressed for the ceremonial parade.

1217
01:37:09,393 --> 01:37:11,623
Yes, sir. What's it all about, sir?

1218
01:37:11,695 --> 01:37:14,498
Well, it's a bit of
a rush job, actually.

1219
01:37:14,631 --> 01:37:18,362
It's to celebrate the coming
to power of the new government.

1220
01:37:18,435 --> 01:37:20,767
Colonel Boniface will
be taking the salute.

1221
01:37:20,837 --> 01:37:24,933
He's now military
governor of the providence.

1222
01:37:25,008 --> 01:37:27,636
I think under the circumstances...

1223
01:37:27,711 --> 01:37:32,944
it might be better if you handed
over the parade to the color sergeant.

1224
01:37:36,052 --> 01:37:38,384
Very good, sir.

1225
01:37:38,455 --> 01:37:42,414
You'll be glad to hear the new government
has elected to stay in the commonwealth.

1226
01:37:42,492 --> 01:37:46,053
So, of course, we shall
be carrying on as before.

1227
01:37:46,129 --> 01:37:48,063
Very well, sir.

1228
01:37:48,131 --> 01:37:50,725
What's going to happen
to Captain Abraham, sir?

1229
01:37:50,800 --> 01:37:55,430
Well, the new president has
given him safe conduct...

1230
01:37:55,505 --> 01:37:58,303
out of the country.

1231
01:37:58,375 --> 01:38:00,570
That's good, sir.

1232
01:38:00,644 --> 01:38:02,578
Yes, but...

1233
01:38:02,646 --> 01:38:06,707
we, um, had to compromise.

1234
